<h2 id=3D"id-03.SD:PaymentDetails(Customer&amp;Staff)-SecurityAspects">Secu=
rity Aspects</h2>
<p>The Galaxy application security is per below.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Authentication</strong>: It will be handled with Ping Federate =
using PKCE flow.</li>
<li><strong>Authorisation</strong>:&nbsp; All authenticated users (customer=
 and staff) will have access to the same properties.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"id-03.SD:PaymentDetails(Customer&amp;Staff)-ErrorHandling">Error =
Handling</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-03.SD:PaymentDetails(Customer&amp;Staff)-Summary:">Summary:</h=
3>
<p>The below error codes should be handled by the UI:</p>
<ul>
<li>Bad Request Error</li>
<li>Server Error</li>
<li>Timeout Error</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Read more here: <a class=3D"" href=3D"https://confluence.srv.wes=
tpac.com.au/x/-AJjVw" rel=3D"nofollow">https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.a=
u/x/-AJjVw</a></strong></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-03.SD:PaymentDetails(Customer&amp;Staff)-Data&amp;InformationM=
odel">Data &amp; Information Model&nbsp;&nbsp;</h2>
<p>All mappings between UI and each service layer listed in below.</p>
<ul>
<li><span>Payment listing UI-Payment Experience API Mapping: <a href=3D"/pa=
ges/viewpage.action?pageId=3D1510495045">Payment Details UI- Payment Experi=
ence API Mapping [ERM 25E2 - February 2025]</a></span></li>
<li>Payment Experience API- Source Systems Data Mapping: <a href=3D"/displa=
y/ARTC/Payment+Experience+API+-+Source+Systems+Mapping">Payment Experience =
API - Source Systems Mapping</a></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"id-03.SD:PaymentDetails(Customer&amp;Staff)-OperationalImpacts">O=
perational Impacts</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-03.SD:PaymentDetails(Customer&amp;Staff)-Logging:"><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Logging:</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">The recommended logging framework =
to use for API development is<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a class=3D"external=
-link" href=3D"http://www.slf4j.org/" rel=3D"nofollow">SLF4J</a><span style=
=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">, and it has<span>&nbsp;</span></span><a class=
=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/plugins/ser=
vlet/search?q=3Dproject%3AWDP+slf4j" rel=3D"nofollow">widest adoption</a><s=
pan style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);"><span>&nbsp;</span>across WDP platform =
APIs as of March 2020: <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/dis=
play/WDPIPAAS/Logging+Framework+-+Java" rel=3D"nofollow">Read more</a> .</s=
pan></p>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">As a general concern, we should ma=
sk any <strong><u>PII</u></strong> data or <u><strong>sensitive</strong> </=
u>identifiers. In this solution, we have two data elements we should mask p=
er below table.</span></p>
<p><br></p>
<h3 id=3D"id-03.SD:PaymentDetails(Customer&amp;Staff)-Security:"><span styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Security:</span></h3>
<p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">In addition to client side data va=
lidation, server-side validation should also be performed to ensure that th=
e correct request is being received from the UI. The <a class=3D"external-l=
ink" href=3D"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/UI-WWW1/repos/wd=
p-ui-expcommon/browse/packages/bootstrap" rel=3D"nofollow">@wdpui/common-mi=
ddleware</a><span>&nbsp;</span>package (part of @wdpui/common-bootstrap) pr=
ovides some middleware to enhance the security of experience APIs. The comm=
on bootstrap is required to be used in all projects unless an exemption is =
received from ISG.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com=
.au/display/MESH/6.3.8+Security" rel=3D"nofollow">Read more here</a>.</span=
></p>
<p><br></p>
